{%- comment -%}
  LE FIGUE — cart packaging chooser (2026-07-21; v3 model 2026-07-22).
  Per-ORDER choice, BOTH FREE: Full packaging (signature box & pouch,
  default) vs Reduced (pouch only). No money involved — the choice is
  recorded as cart/order attribute "Packaging" so fulfillment sees it on
  every order (admin: Additional details). The radios are literally
  named attributes[Packaging], so the native cart-form checkout POST
  carries the choice with zero JS; assets/lefigue-custom.js ALSO
  persists it to /cart/update.js on every toggle (covers dynamic
  checkout buttons that bypass the form) and remembers the preference
  in localStorage lf:packaging (absent = full).
  History: v1 = hidden +$2 product (10223951118634, now DRAFT; JS still
  scrubs legacy lines, cart templates still skip type-Packaging items);
  v2 = −$2 code REDUCED-PACKAGING (node 1632895303978, DEACTIVATED).
  Rendered in sections/quick-cart.liquid + sections/main-cart.liquid.
  Styles: custom.css Edit #26.

  Accepts: context — 'drawer' | 'page' (unused for the input name — the
  two renders live in different <form>s, so the groups stay separate).
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign lfp_real_items = 0
  for item in cart.items
    unless item.product.type == 'Packaging'
      assign lfp_real_items = lfp_real_items | plus: 1
    endunless
  endfor
-%}

{%- if lfp_real_items > 0 -%}
  <div class="lf-pack" data-lf-pack>
    <div class="lfp-head">Packaging</div>
    <label class="lfp-opt">
      <input type="radio" name="attributes[Packaging]" value="Full packaging" checked>
      <span class="lfp-txt">
        <span class="lfp-t">Full packaging</span>
        <span class="lfp-d">LE FIGUE&rsquo;s signature box &amp; pouch</span>
      </span>
    </label>
    <label class="lfp-opt">
      <input type="radio" name="attributes[Packaging]" value="Reduced packaging">
      <span class="lfp-txt">
        <span class="lfp-t">Reduced packaging</span>
        <span class="lfp-d">Delivered in a LE FIGUE pouch</span>
      </span>
    </label>
  </div>
{%- endif -%}
